/*
We want to overload the 1.0/1.1 functions, but those function are defined in OpenGL32.dll/GL.so. On Linux, this seems to cause problems
with external shared objects that are linked to the application (CgGL.so, for example). To work around this, we just implement the 1.0/1.1
functions ourselves, which will call either __native_* or __debug_*, depending on whether or not debugging is enabled on the context.
Function pointers beginning with just two underscores, such as gtglGetError(), will point to either the corresponding __native_* or
__debug_* function.
*/

